---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro"

---
<MainLayout title="Yeji Fusebox Project" seoTitle="Fusebox" seoDesc="Connecting to Create.">

<div class="mt-20 mx-20 font-serif" >
  <div class="flex align-middle items-center justify-center gap-3">
    <img src="/assets/images/smiley.png" alt="smiley face" class=" w-20 max-h-fit shrink-0 pb-4">
    <div>
      <h1 class="header pr-6  text-blue-600">Fusebox</h1>
      <h3 class="font-sans text-neutral-400">Connecting to Create.</h3>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- DETAILS -->
  <div class="flex mt-4 gap-10 font-sans text-sm justify-center">
    <!-- timeline -->
    <div class="w-32 leading-4">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-xl">Timeline:</h1>
      9.2023 - 5.2024
    </div>
    <!-- team -->
    <div class="w-32 leading-4">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-xl">Team:</h1>
      Rory An, Paris Little, Joanna Poon, Lauren Graham, Henry Groome
    </div>
    <!-- role --> 
    <div class="w-32 leading-4">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-xl">Role:</h1>
      <p>Project Lead & Product Manager, Full-Stack Developer, Designer</p>
    </div>
    <!-- tools -->
    <div class="w-32 leading-4">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-xl">Tools:</h1>
      <p>HTML, CSS, JavaScript, PHP, SQL</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="mt-16">
    <h1 class="text-xl text-neutral-400">Fusebox started from my <span class="text-blue-600">frustration</span> in finding project partners outside of my network. This led me to the question:</h1>
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-italic">How do we connect USC creatives?</h1>
    <p class="font-sans text-sm w-1/2">Alongside my team of 5, Fusebox was born: a browser-based platform that aims to connect creatives from different disciplines and facilitate collaboration. Because we believe that the best creations are born when people from diverse backgrounds and skills come together, our platform aimed to provide a space for makers to discover other collaborators with the skills to bring their passion projects to lifeâ€”offering functionality like the abilitiy to post your project and needed roles, and to find an active feed of projects and users.</p>
  </div>



</div>